s regulations. Mr. Pierce also represents hundreds of clients in the hospitality industry, including bars, clubs, restaurants and hotels, and is highly experienced in State Liquor Authority application and compliance issues and actions.<\/p><p>Mr. Pierce routinely prepares and negotiates intellectual property agreements (including license, coexistence, and website agreements). He also is experienced in intellectual property litigation, including matters connected with trademarks, copyrights, right of publicity and anti-counterfeiting.<\/p><p>In addition to Mr. Pierce\u2019s corporate transactional practice, he also regularly represents clients in a wide variety of commercial litigations in both state and federal court. Mr. Pierce has had first-chair and second-chair responsibilities in litigations for several different clients including bench and jury trials in both state and federal court. He is known to colleagues and clients alike as a focused and thoughtful litigator.<\/p><p>Aaron was selected for inclusion in New York Super Lawyers \u2013 Rising Stars Edition, Thomson Reuters, 2015-2019, and was also included in New York Super Lawyers, Thomson Reuters, for 2015-2022. Aaron regularly teaches Entrepreneurial and Entertainment Law seminars and classes, and is a faculty member at the National Academy of Continuing Legal Education, The Marino Institute of Continuing Legal Education, and Parsons School of Design.<\/p><p>Mr. Pierce has been intrinsically involved in the entertainment industry in New York City for 25 years, and represents some of the largest venues and concert promoters in the country, provides counsel throughout many segments of the entertainment industry, including film, music, theater, and publishing, and serves as general counsel to several NYC-based artist management companies. Mr. Pierce also provides consulting services to up-and-coming artists, artist managers, art galleries, independent labels, film producers, and art curators.<\/p><h4>EDUCATION:<\/h4><p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">J.D., Fordham Law School, 2009 &#8211; Archibald R. Public Service Award\u00a0 &#8211; Magna Cum\u00a0 Laude<\/span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><br \/><\/span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">B.A., Political Science and Theatre &#8211; State University of New York at Buffalo, 1997, Magna Cum Laude<br \/><\/span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">University College Dublin School of Law \u2013 International Law Studies \u2013 2007<br \/><\/span><span style=\"font-size: 16.5px; font-weight: 400;\">Queen&#8217;s University Belfast School of Law \u2013 International Law Studies \u2013 2007<\/span><\/p><h4>PROFESSIONAL ASSOCIATIONS AND MEMBERSHIPS:<\/h4><p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Board Member \u2013 WP Theater Board of Directors<br \/><\/span>New York State Bar Association<br \/>New York County Bar Association<br \/>New York City Bar Association<br \/>American Bar Association<br \/>New York Chamber of Commerce<\/p><h4>BAR ADMISSIONS:<\/h4><p>New York State, New Jersey, District of Columbia<br \/>United States District Court, Southern District of New York<br \/>United States District Court, Eastern District of New York<br \/><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">U.S. Court Of Appeals, Second Circuit<br \/><\/span><\/p><h4>REPRESENTATIVE MATTERS<\/h4><ul><li>Personal Counsel to President of Live Nation \u2013 New York<\/li><li>Counsel \u2013 Fortune Films USA, Inc.<\/li><li>Counsel \u2013 Wonder Wheel Productions<\/li><li>General Counsel \u2013 Chelsea Film Festival<\/li><li>General Counsel \u2013 Bushwick Film Festival<\/li><li>General Counsel \u2013 The Bowery Ballroom. NYC<\/li><li>General Counsel \u2013 The Williamsburg Music Hall, NYC<\/li><li>General Counsel \u2013 The Mercury Lounge, NYC<\/li><li>Counsel \u2013 141 Entertainment<\/li><li>General Counsel to numerous NYC and Long Island Art Galleries<\/li><li>Board Member of the WP Theater, the nation\u2019s most recognized and award-winning Off-Broadway Company <span style=\"font-size: 16.5px; font-weight: 400;\">dedicated to developing, producing, and promoting the work of women+ at every stage of their careers.<\/span><\/li><li>General Counsel to several award-winning independent film companies having helped many take their films to festivals and critical acclaim across the globe including Sundance and Cannes.\u00a0<\/li><li>Represented a plaintiff through to verdict in a federal civil jury trial in the Southern District. Defendant found to have misappropriated hundreds of thousands of dollars in a scheme involving numerous high-end \/ luxury automobiles.\u00a0<\/li><li>Successfully represented numerous individuals and companies in intellectual property disputes regarding copyright and trademark infringement. Has obtained favorable settlements for marketing agencies, accounting firms, clothing brands, film companies, and music venues.\u00a0<\/li><li>Represented many clients in a variety of defamation cases. Recently obtained a 6 figure settlement on behalf of a client against a major regional newspaper.<\/li><li>Represented numerous bars and restaurants as defendants in lawsuits filed against them by disabled persons for both structural buildouts and website access violations under the American Disabilities Act.<\/li><li>Recently achieved a preliminary injunction against one of the largest private universities in the United States, effectively halting a multi-million dollar construction operation until favorable disability protocols were set in place.<\/li><li>Represented dozens of client in commercial landlord\/tenant disputes including several through to a successful verdict at trial.<\/li><li>Represented numerous creditors in successful collections, including court costs, attorney\u2019s fees and accrued interest.<\/li><li>Represents large-scale international manufacturing clients in disputes and litigations against subcontractors and distributors.<\/li><li>Represents clients in construction\/contracting disputes. Pierce &amp; Kwok LLP regularly represents multi-million dollar construction companies and developers. We understand these often complex disputes from a wide variety of angles.<\/li><li>Successfully represented numerous film production companies in financial and investment disputes litigated in both state and federal courts.<\/li><li>Represents several gaming and tech companies in intellectual property disputes regarding the technical details and ownership of computer coding.<\/li><\/ul>\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/section>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t","protected":false},"featured_media":2649,"template":"","meta":{"_acf_changed":false,"site-sidebar-layout":"no-sidebar","site-content-layout":"page-builder","ast-site-content-layout":"full-width-container","site-content-style":"unboxed","site-sidebar-style":"unboxed","ast-global-header-display":"","ast-banner-title-visibility":"","ast-main-header-display":"","ast-hfb-above-header-display":"","ast-hfb-below-header-display":"","ast-hfb-mobile-header-display":"","site-post-title":"disabled","ast-breadcrumbs-content":"","ast-featured-img":"disabled","footer-sml-layout":"","theme-transparent-header-meta":"default","adv-header-id-meta":"","stick-header-meta":"","header-above-stick-meta":"","header-main-stick-meta":"","header-below-stick-meta":"","astra-migrate-meta-layouts":"set","ast-page-background-enabled":"default","ast-page-background-meta":{"desktop":{"background-color":"","background-image":"","background-repeat":"repeat","background-position":"center center","background-size":"auto","background-attachment":"scroll","background-type":"","background-media":"","overlay-type":"","overlay-color":"","overlay-opacity":"","overlay-gradient":""},"tablet":{"background-color":"","background-image":"","background-repeat":"repeat","background-position":"center center","background-size":"auto","background-attachment":"scroll","background-type":"","background-media":""